== Introduction == <!--T:132-->

<!--T:2-->
The [[Image:Workbench_PartDesign.svg|24px]] [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign Workbench]] provides tools for modeling solid components. It is mostly focused on creating mechanical components that can be manufactured and assembled into a finished product. Nevertheless, the created solids can be used in general for any other purpose such as [[BIM_Workbench|BIM modeling]], [[FEM_Workbench|finite element analysis]], or [[CAM_Workbench|machining and 3D printing]].

<!--T:117-->
The PartDesign Workbench uses a feature editing methodology. A component is represented by the Body object container. The Body defines the local coordinate system and contains the cumulative features that define the component.

